          fun that half the audience wanted to audition for the next play.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed text-left">
          Next up were two one acts in a friend’s living room, a musical with a
          live band at <a
            href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/D4fMEk4VDWkvevCt8"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
            >Ruth’s Table Community Center</a
          >, and a variety show at <a
            href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/1v7K1fvuS41F5pUw6"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">The Nook</a
          >. We talked about going back to our casual basement roots this year…
          instead we’re here with a two act musical and a 5-piece band. Oops!
          Our cast & crew are entirely made up of friends, word-of-mouth
          acquaintances, and people who attended previous productions and
          thought: “Maybe I could do that!” We would love for you to get
          involved and discover (or rediscover) the magic of the theater arts.
          Join us!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
